            <p>It's finally happening, apparently. After a protracted and extremely tumultusous decade of development, <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/the-wolf-among-us-2">The Wolf Among Us 2</a> is supposedly now launching next year. And there's a remaster of the much-loved original on the way to tide us over until then.</p>
<p>First announced in 2017, The Wolf Among Us 2 - the sequel to developer Telltale's 2013 video game adaptation of Bill Willingham's Fables comics - has been on and off again throughout the last ten years. All seemed lost when <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/the-walking-dead-developer-telltale-games-reportedly-lays-off-the-majority-of-its-staff">Telltale closed its doors in 2018</a>, but it was somewhat miraculously <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/telltales-the-wolf-among-us-2-just-got-re-announced">resurrected in 2019</a> - only to disappear again in 2023.</p>

<figure>
